foreProfileModule.name: foreProfileModule
foreProfileModule.contactinfo: Postal: FORE Systems Inc. 1000 FORE Drive Warrendale, PA 15086-7502 Tel: +1 724 742 6900 Email: nm_mibs@fore.com Web: http://www.fore.com
foreProfileModule.description: This MIB module defines several profile tables that facilitate the creation of FR/ATM and FUNI services and connections.

profileLmiEntry.name: profileLmiEntry
profileLmiEntry.description: An entry in the LMI profile table.

profileLmiIndex.name: profileLmiIndex
profileLmiIndex.description: This objects identifies the index of a profile entry in this table.

profileLmiRowStatus.name: profileLmiRowStatus
profileLmiRowStatus.description: This object is used to create new rows and delete existing rows in this table.

profileLmiName.name: profileLmiName
profileLmiName.description: This object specifies the symbolic name assigned to this profile for user reference.

profileLmiFlavour.name: profileLmiFlavour
profileLmiFlavour.description: This object specifies the type of the LMI protocol used over this FR service. This object corresponds to frLportVCSigProtocol in RFC1604 and frDlcmiState in RFC1315.

profileLmiT391.name: profileLmiT391
profileLmiT391.description: The value of this object identifies the User-side T391 link integrity verification polling timer value (in seconds) for this UNI/NNI logical port. If the logical port is not performing user-side procedures, then this value is equal to noSuchName. This object applies to Q.933 Annex A and T1.617 Annex D. This object corresponds to frMgtVCSigUserT391 in RFC1604 and frDlcmiPollingInterval in RFC1315.

profileLmiN391.name: profileLmiN391
profileLmiN391.description: The value of this object identifies the User-side N391 full status polling cycle value for this UNI/NNI logical port. If the logical port is not performing user-side procedures, then this value is equal to noSuchName. This object applies to Q.933 Annex A and T1.617 Annex D. This object corresponds to frMgtVCSigUserN391 in RFC1604 and frDlcmiFullEnquiryInterval.

profileLmiT392.name: profileLmiT392
profileLmiT392.description: The value of this object identifies the Network- side T392 polling verification timer value in seconds (nT2 for LMI) for this UNI/NNI logical port. If the logical port is not performing network-side procedures, then this value is equal to noSuchName. This object applies to Q.933 Annex A, LMI and T1.617 Annex D. This object corresponds to frMgtVCSigNetT392 in RFC1604.

profileLmiN392.name: profileLmiN392
profileLmiN392.description: The value of this object identifies the Network- side N392 error threshold value (nN2 for LMI) for this UNI/NNI logical port. If the logical port is not performing network-side procedures, then this value is equal to noSuchName. This object applies to Q.933 Annex A, T1.617 Annex D and LMI. This object corresponds to frMgtVCSigNetN392 and frMgtVCSigUserN392 when the LMI role is network and user respectively in RFC1604, and frDlcmiErrorThreshold in RFC1315.

profileLmiN393.name: profileLmiN393
profileLmiN393.description: The value of this object identifies the Network- side N393 monitored events count value (nN3 for LMI) for this UNI/NNI logical port. If the logical port is not performing network-side procedures, then this value is equal to noSuchName. This object applies to Q.933 Annex A, LMI and T1.617 Annex D. This object corresponds to frMgtVCSigNetN393 and frMgtVCSigUserN393 when the LMI role is network and user respectively in RFC1604, and frDlcmiMonitoredEvents in RFC1315.

profileLminT3.name: profileLminT3
profileLminT3.description: The value of this object identifies the Network-side nT3 timer in seconds (for nN4 status enquires received) value for this FR service. This object applies only to LMI(STRATACOM) flavour. The allowable values include 5, 10, 15, 20, 25 and 30 seconds. This object corresponds to frMgtVCSigNetnT3 in RFC1604.

profileLmiDirection.name: profileLmiDirection
profileLmiDirection.description: The value of this object identifies the Local In-Channel Signaling Procedure that is used for this UNI/NNI logical port. The UNI/NNI logical port can be performing only user-to-network network-side procedures or bidirectional procedures.This object corresponds to frMgtVCSigProced in RFC1604.

profileLmiRole.name: profileLmiRole
profileLmiRole.description: This object specifies the role of operation of this FR service - user (DTE) or network (DCE)

profileLmiRefCnt.name: profileLmiRefCnt
profileLmiRefCnt.description: This object identifies the number of services that are currently referring to this profile.

profileFrRateEntry.name: profileFrRateEntry
profileFrRateEntry.description: An entry in the FR rate profile table.

profileFrRateIndex.name: profileFrRateIndex
profileFrRateIndex.description: This object identifies the index of a profile entry in this table.

profileFrRateRowStatus.name: profileFrRateRowStatus
profileFrRateRowStatus.description: This object is used to create new rows and delete existing rows in this table.

profileFrRateName.name: profileFrRateName
profileFrRateName.description: This object identifies the symbolic name assigned to this profile used for user reference.

profileFrRateInBc.name: profileFrRateInBc
profileFrRateInBc.description: This object represents the committed burst size (bits) in the ingress direction of a connection. This object corresponds to frPVCEndptInBc in RFC1604 and frCircuitCommittedBurst in RFC1315.

profileFrRateInBe.name: profileFrRateInBe
profileFrRateInBe.description: This object represents the excess burst size (bits) in the ingress direction of a connection. This object corresponds to frPVCEndptInBe in RFC1604 and frCircuitExcessBurst in RFC1315.

profileFrRateInCir.name: profileFrRateInCir
profileFrRateInCir.description: This object represents the committed information rate (kbps) in the ingress direction of a connection. This object corresponds to frPVCEndptInCIR in RFC1604 and frCircuitThroughput in RFC1315.

profileFrRateOutBc.name: profileFrRateOutBc
profileFrRateOutBc.description: This object represents the committed burst size (bits) in the egress direction of a connection. This object corresponds frPVCEndptOutBc in RFC1604.

profileFrRateOutBe.name: profileFrRateOutBe
profileFrRateOutBe.description: This object represents the excess burst size (bits) in the egress direction of a connection. This object corresponds frPVCEndptOutBe in RFC1604.

profileFrRateOutCir.name: profileFrRateOutCir
profileFrRateOutCir.description: This object represents the committed information rate (kbps) in the egress direction of a connection. This object corresponds frPVCEndptOutCIR in RFC1604.

profileFrRateMinBc.name: profileFrRateMinBc
profileFrRateMinBc.description: This object represents the minimum committed burst size (bits) which can be set on a connection by rate adaptation.

profileFrRateCmPeriod.name: profileFrRateCmPeriod
profileFrRateCmPeriod.description: This object represents the time period (msec) during which BECNs are monitored before the rate adaptation mechanism decides to change the current committed burst size in the egress direction.

profileFrRateRefCnt.name: profileFrRateRefCnt
profileFrRateRefCnt.description: This object identifies the number of connections that are currently referring to this profile entry.

profileFuniEntry.name: profileFuniEntry
profileFuniEntry.description: An entry in the FUNI profile table.

profileFuniIndex.name: profileFuniIndex
profileFuniIndex.description: This object identifies the index of a profile entry in this table.

profileFuniRowStatus.name: profileFuniRowStatus
profileFuniRowStatus.description: This object is used to create new rows and delete existing rows in this table.

profileFuniName.name: profileFuniName
profileFuniName.description: This object specifies the symbolic name assigned to this profile for user reference.

profileFuniIlmiVpi.name: profileFuniIlmiVpi
profileFuniIlmiVpi.description: This object represents VPI value used by ILMI over this FUNI interface. This object corresponds to funiIfConfIlmiVpi in FUNI MIB.

profileFuniIlmiVci.name: profileFuniIlmiVci
profileFuniIlmiVci.description: This object represents VCI value used by ILMI over this FUNI service. This object corresponds to funiIfConfIlmiVci in FUNI MIB.

profileFuniSigVpi.name: profileFuniSigVpi
profileFuniSigVpi.description: This object represents VPI value used for the signalling channel over this FUNI service. This object corresponds to funiIfConfSigVpi in FUNI MIB.

profileFuniSigVci.name: profileFuniSigVci
profileFuniSigVci.description: This object represents VCI value used for the signalling channel over this FUNI service. This object corresponds to funiIfConfSigVci in FUNI MIB.

profileFuniMinVci.name: profileFuniMinVci
profileFuniMinVci.description: This object represents minimal numeric value allowed to be used as a VCI on any user connection over this FUNI service.

profileFuniMaxVci.name: profileFuniMaxVci
profileFuniMaxVci.description: This object represents maximal numeric value allowed to be used as a VCI on any user connection over this FUNI service.

profileFuniIlmiSupport.name: profileFuniIlmiSupport
profileFuniIlmiSupport.description: This object specifies that an ILMI instance is to be supported on this FUNI service if the mode is set to enabled. This object corresponds to funiIfConfIlmiSupport in FUNI MIB.

profileFuniSigSupport.name: profileFuniSigSupport
profileFuniSigSupport.description: This object specifies that a signalling instance is to be supported on this FUNI service if the mode is set to enabled. This object corresponds to funiIfConfSigSupport in FUNI MIB.

profileFuniOamSupport.name: profileFuniOamSupport
profileFuniOamSupport.description: This object specifies that OAM cells and frames are to be transferred on this FUNI service if the mode is set to enabled. This object corresponds to funiIfConfOamSupport in FUNI MIB.

profileFuniActiveVpiBits.name: profileFuniActiveVpiBits
profileFuniActiveVpiBits.description: The value of this object identifies the maximum number of active VPI bits configured for use at this FUNI interface. At the ATM FUNI, this value will be smaller than or equal to 4 and 8 when the FUNI header size is two and four bytes respectively, as specified by the profile attribute profileFuniConfMode. This object corresponds to atmInterfaceMaxActiveVpiBits in the ATOM MIB.

profileFuniActiveVciBits.name: profileFuniActiveVciBits
profileFuniActiveVciBits.description: The value of this object identifies the maximum number of active VCI bits configured for use at this FUNI interface. At the ATM FUNI, this value will be smaller than or equal to 6 and 16 when the FUNI header size is two and four bytes respectively, as specified by the profile attribute profileFuniConfMode. This object corresponds to atmInterfaceMaxActiveVciBits in the ATOM MIB.

profileFuniConfMode.name: profileFuniConfMode
profileFuniConfMode.description: The value of this object specifies whether a 2 or 4 byte header is present in each FUNI frame header over a FUNI service. For mode1a, mode1b and mode 3, a 2-byte header is used. For mode 4, a 4-byte header is used. This object corresponds to funiIfConfMode in FUNI MIB.

profileFuniFcsBits.name: profileFuniFcsBits
profileFuniFcsBits.description: This object specifies whether a 16- or 32-bit FCS is used in each FUNI frame header over this FUNI logical interface.

profileFuniHdrBytes.name: profileFuniHdrBytes
profileFuniHdrBytes.description: This object specifies whether a 2- or 4-bytes header is used in each FUNI frame header over this FUNI logical interface.

profileFuniAal34Support.name: profileFuniAal34Support
profileFuniAal34Support.description: This object specifies whether support for AAL3/4 VCCs shall be allowed on this FUNI logical interface. A FUNI logical interface that cannot support AAL3/4 VCCs must only allow the value disabled(2).

profileFuniRefCnt.name: profileFuniRefCnt
profileFuniRefCnt.description: The value of this object identifies the number of services that are referring to this profile.

profileFrf8Entry.name: profileFrf8Entry
profileFrf8Entry.description: An entry in the FRF.8 profile table.

profileFrf8Index.name: profileFrf8Index
profileFrf8Index.description: This object identifies the index of a profile in this table.

profileFrf8RowStatus.name: profileFrf8RowStatus
profileFrf8RowStatus.description: This object is used to create new rows and delete existing rows in this table.

profileFrf8Name.name: profileFrf8Name
profileFrf8Name.description: This object specifies the symbolic name assigned to this profile for user reference.

profileFrf8DeMode.name: profileFrf8DeMode
profileFrf8DeMode.description: If the DE mode is set to mapped, the DE field in the Q922 core frame is mapped to the ATM CLP filled of every cell generated by the segmentation process of the AAL5 PDU containing the information of that frame. Otherwise, the ATM CLP of every ATM cell generated by the segmentation process of the AAL5 PDU containing the information of that frame is set to a constant value specified by the configuration parameter profileFrf8DefaultClp.

profileFrf8ClpMode.name: profileFrf8ClpMode
profileFrf8ClpMode.description: If the CLP mode is set to mapped, then the FR/ATM service interworking function will set the DE field of the Q922 core frame, provided that one or more cells belonging to this frame has its CLP field set. Otherwise, the DE field of the Q922 core frame is set to a constant value specified by the configuration parameter profileFrf8DefaultDe.

profileFrf8FecnMode.name: profileFrf8FecnMode
profileFrf8FecnMode.description: If the Fecn mode is set to mapped, the FECN field in the Q922 core frame is mapped to the ATM EFCI field of every cell generated by the segmentation process of the AAL5 PDU containing the information of that frame. This mode provides congestion indication to the end-points where higher layer protocol entities might be involved in traffic control mechanisms. Otherwise, the EFCI field of cells generated by the segmentation process of the AAL5 PDU containing the information of the frame is always set to congestion-not-experienced.

profileFrf8DefaultDe.name: profileFrf8DefaultDe
profileFrf8DefaultDe.description: This object represents the DE bit value of all generated FR frame headers if the CLP mode is set to ignored.

profileFrf8DefaultClp.name: profileFrf8DefaultClp
profileFrf8DefaultClp.description: This object represents the CLP bit value of all generated ATM cell headers if the DE mode is set to ignored.

profileFrf8Protocols.name: profileFrf8Protocols
profileFrf8Protocols.description: This object represents a binary map which lists all possible encapsulation translation protocols over this FRF.8 IWF instance. Any combination of the specified encapsulation modes will be supported. The binary map assignment is defined as below: ethernet (0000000000001) ethernetFcs (0000000000010) tokenRing (0000000000100) tokenRingFcs (0000000001000) ipRouted (0000000010000) arp (0000000100000) ipx (0000001000000) sna (0000010000000) fddi (0000100000000) fddiFcs (0001000000000) x.25/75 (0010000000000) 802.6 (0100000000000) routedIso (1000000000000) or any combinations of the binary map. The allowable range of the input is from 0 to 8191. This object corresponds to frf8ProtProtocol in fore-frf8 MIB.

profileFrf8RefCnt.name: profileFrf8RefCnt
profileFrf8RefCnt.description: The value of this object identifies the number of connections that are currently referring to this profile.

profileServiceEntry.name: profileServiceEntry
profileServiceEntry.description: An entry in the generic service profile table.

profileServiceIndex.name: profileServiceIndex
profileServiceIndex.description: This object identifies the index of a profile in this table.

profileServiceRowStatus.name: profileServiceRowStatus
profileServiceRowStatus.description: This object is used to create new rows and delete existing rows in this table.

profileServiceName.name: profileServiceName
profileServiceName.description: This object specifies the symbolic name assigned to this profile for user reference.

profileServiceAccRate.name: profileServiceAccRate
profileServiceAccRate.description: This object represents the access rate of the service (kbps).

profileServiceMaxVccs.name: profileServiceMaxVccs
profileServiceMaxVccs.description: The maximum number of virtual circuits supported in this service. This object corresponds to frDlcmiMaxSupportedVCs in RFC1315 and funiIfExtConfVccs in fore-funi MIB.

profileServiceMaxPayloadSize.name: profileServiceMaxPayloadSize
profileServiceMaxPayloadSize.description: This object represents the maximum payload size (bytes) supported by the service. This object corresponds to frPVCEndptInMaxFrameSize and frPVCEndptOutMaxFrameSize in RFC1604.

profileServiceInBwOb.name: profileServiceInBwOb
profileServiceInBwOb.description: This object represents the bandwidth overbooking (percentage) of the service in the inbound direction. If the percentage is bigger than 100%, it is overbooking; otherwise it is underbooking.

profileServiceOutBwOb.name: profileServiceOutBwOb
profileServiceOutBwOb.description: This object represents the bandwidth overbooking (percentage) of the service in the outbound direction. If the percentage is bigger than 100%, it is overbooking; otherwise it is underbooking.

profileServiceRefCnt.name: profileServiceRefCnt
profileServiceRefCnt.description: The value of this object identifies the number of services that are currently referring to this profile.

profileEpdPpdEntry.name: profileEpdPpdEntry
profileEpdPpdEntry.description: An entry in the EPD/PPD profile table.

profileEpdPpdIndex.name: profileEpdPpdIndex
profileEpdPpdIndex.description: This object identifies the index of a profile in this table.

profileEpdPpdRowStatus.name: profileEpdPpdRowStatus
profileEpdPpdRowStatus.description: This object is used to create new rows and delete existing rows in this table.

profileEpdPpdName.name: profileEpdPpdName
profileEpdPpdName.description: This object specifies the symbolic name assigned to this profile for user reference.

profileEpdPpdPriority.name: profileEpdPpdPriority
profileEpdPpdPriority.description: This object specifies the EPD/PPD priority queue the connection is assigned.

profileEpdPpdClp0Epd.name: profileEpdPpdClp0Epd
profileEpdPpdClp0Epd.description: This object specifies whether the EPD/PPD controller discards CLP=0 traffic after the Clp0Epd threshold has been hit.

profileEpdPpdClp1Ppd.name: profileEpdPpdClp1Ppd
profileEpdPpdClp1Ppd.description: This object specifies whether the EPD/PPD controller discards CLP=1 traffic after the Clp1Ppd threshold has been hit.

profileEpdPpdClp1Epd.name: profileEpdPpdClp1Epd
profileEpdPpdClp1Epd.description: This object specifies whether the EPD/PPD controller discards CLP=1 traffic after the Clp1Epd threshold has been hit.

profileEpdPpdRefCnt.name: profileEpdPpdRefCnt
profileEpdPpdRefCnt.description: The value of this object identifies the number of connections that are currently referring to this profile.

profileFrf5Entry.name: profileFrf5Entry
profileFrf5Entry.description: An entry in the FRF.5 profile table.

profileFrf5Index.name: profileFrf5Index
profileFrf5Index.description: This object identifies the index of a profile in this table. Indices 1 though 20 are reserved for system defaults

profileFrf5RowStatus.name: profileFrf5RowStatus
profileFrf5RowStatus.description: This object is used to create new rows and delete existing rows in this table.

profileFrf5Name.name: profileFrf5Name
profileFrf5Name.description: This object specifies the symbolic name assigned to this profile for user reference.

profileFrf5DeMode.name: profileFrf5DeMode
profileFrf5DeMode.description: If the DE mode is set to mapped, the DE field in the FR_SSCS frame is mapped to the ATM CLP filled of every cell generated by the segmentation process of the AAL5 PDU containing the information of that frame. Otherwise, if the DE mode is set to ignored, the ATM CLP of every ATM cell generated by the segmentation process of the AAL5 PDU containing the information of that frame is set to a constant value specified by the configuration parameter profileFrf5DefaultClp.

profileFrf5ClpFrsscsDeMode.name: profileFrf5ClpFrsscsDeMode
profileFrf5ClpFrsscsDeMode.description: If the CLP mode is set to mapped, the FR/ATM network interworking function will set the DE field of the Q922 core frame, provided that one or more cells belonging to this frame has its CLP field set, or the DE bit of FR_SSCS frame is set. Otherwise, if the CLP mode is set to ignored, the DE bit of FR_SSCS frame is copied to the Q922 core frame.

profileFrf5DefaultClp.name: profileFrf5DefaultClp
profileFrf5DefaultClp.description: This object represents the CLP bit value of all generated ATM cell headers if the DE mode is set to ignored.

profileFrf5MaxDlcis.name: profileFrf5MaxDlcis
profileFrf5MaxDlcis.description: The maximum number of virtual circuits supported in this VCC.

profileFrf5MaxPayloadSize.name: profileFrf5MaxPayloadSize
profileFrf5MaxPayloadSize.description: This object represents the maximum payload size (bytes) supported by the VCC.

profileFrf5RefCnt.name: profileFrf5RefCnt
profileFrf5RefCnt.description: The value of this object identifies the number of connections that are currently referring to this profile.
